    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.9.8-9_0001-2" />
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE ARMY AND NAVY CLUB
                        <lb/>
                    WASHINGTON</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Jan'y. 22, 1922.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I wrote to you a couple of days ago, addressing my letter to Bancroft, Neb., instead of Branson, Mo., where I find you were when you last wrote to me. No doubt my letter will be forwarded to you, but for fear not, I am writing again.</p>
                
                <!--text missing here, suspect that the back of the first page, which appeared to have writing on it, was never scanned-->
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.9.8-9_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
                <p>of the Military Service Institution (1890 and &#8212; ?). If not, I will try to send them to you. The former, including the heroic outbreak at Camp Robinson, is an epic in itself.</p>
                
                <p>I also invited you to attend the annual dinner of the Order of Indian Wars, in February or March, in Wash-nig, as my guest, date not yet fixed. Kindly keep me informed by postal card of your whereabouts on lecture tour, so that I may write or wire you date. I hope you are going to lecture in Washington, while east.</p>
                
                <p>I think Mrs. <unclear>Custer</unclear> lives in New York City. I will try to get her address.</p>
                
                <p>I am greatly interested in your grand epic <title>"The Song of the Indian Wars."</title></p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With kind regards,</salute>
                    <salute>Most faithfully yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>H.R. Lemly</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
